      • configureLayers

        public void configureLayers​(java.util.List<java.util.List<double[]>> layer_weights,
                            java.util.List<double[]> layer_activations,
                            java.util.List<double[]> layer_biases)
                     throws InvalidArgumentVectorSize
        Configure network weights and biases to some predefined values.
        Parameters:
        layer_weights - List of layer weights where each element is a List of link weights of each node in the layer.
        layer_activations - List of initial activation values for network where each element is an array of values for each layer nodes.
        layer_biases - List of initial bias values for network where each element is an array of values for each layer nodes.
        Throws:
        InvalidArgumentVectorSize - if any of the argument vector size differs with the corresponding network configuration.

      • testNetwork

        public double[] testNetwork()
                     throws InvalidArgumentVectorSize,
                            java.lang.InterruptedException,
                            java.io.IOException
        To start testing of network targetting the test set defined by the DataAdapter object passed.
        Returns:
        array of double values each indicating rms error between actual and predicted values.
        Throws:
        InvalidArgumentVectorSize - on encounter of non-matching length between network input nodes and the input vector size stored in DataAdapter
        java.lang.InterruptedException - on interrupton of running Perceptron Thread.
        java.io.IOException - if output file stream does not work properly.

      • trainNetwork

        public double[] trainNetwork()
                      throws InvalidArgumentVectorSize,
                             java.lang.InterruptedException,
                             java.io.IOException,
                             NoSuchLayerException
        Initiates training of networking by feeding the training partition of dataset from DataAdapter.
        Returns:
        array of rms errors occurred at last stage of retraining by each input. Length is equal to Training data set.
        Throws:
        InvalidArgumentVectorSize - on encounter of mismatch length of input or output vector size and the network input or output width.
        java.lang.InterruptedException - on interruption of running Perceptron
        java.io.IOException - on error occurred during writing the output to output file stream attached to DataAdapter.
        NoSuchLayerException - occurs when network access some layer undefined.

      • getNetworkOutput

        public double[] getNetworkOutput()
        Retrieves the network output at any stage.
        Returns:
        the output values of each output node as an array.

      • propagateInput

        public void propagateInput​(double[] input)
                    throws InvalidArgumentVectorSize,
                           java.lang.InterruptedException
        Run network against an input value. It assigns the the input values to input layer nodes first then propagates them through the network by starting execution of each layer in order.
        Parameters:
        input - input vector that is supposed to be feeded to the network.
        Throws:
        InvalidArgumentVectorSize - on encounter of unequal input vector size with the network width.
        java.lang.InterruptedException - on interruption of any running Perceptron node.

      • calcAndBackPropagateError

        public double[] calcAndBackPropagateError​(double[] targetOutput)
                                   throws InvalidArgumentVectorSize,
                                          NoSuchLayerException
        To calculate error occurred at the output node with actual value and then propagate them backwards by calibration of link weights and node bias values using gradient decent calculus.
        Parameters:
        targetOutput - the actual output for the last feeded input.
        Returns:
        errors at each node in the output layer.
        Throws:
        InvalidArgumentVectorSize - on encounter of invalid size of @param targetOutput with the output width of network.
        NoSuchLayerException - if network configuration is invalid and an undefined layer is accessed.
